"Tzanis C.","On the relationship between total ozone and temperature in the troposphere and the lower stratosphere",2009,"International Journal of Remote Sensing","30","23",,"6075","6084",,,10.1080/01431160902798429,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77449129150&partnerID=40&md5=be067c3e62a30a2abff4cae96709fd8d","Department of Applied Physics, University of Athens, Panepistimiopolis Build. Phys. 5, 15784 Athens, Greece","Tzanis, C., Department of Applied Physics, University of Athens, Panepistimiopolis Build. Phys. 5, 15784 Athens, Greece","Total ozone and atmospheric temperature are two variables that are closely connected with two important environmental problems: ozone depletion and global warming. Vertical temperature profiles and column ozone data are analysed to explore the relationship between these two variables at various levels in the troposphere and lower stratosphere over Athens, Greece during the period 1992-2004. The results obtained show an out-of-phase relationship between total ozone and temperature in the troposphere and an in-phase relationship in the lower stratosphere. Such a phase change is characteristic of all seasons. © 2009 Taylor & Francis.",,"Athens , Greece; Column ozone; Environmental problems; In-phase; Lower stratosphere; Out of phase; Ozone depletion; Phase Change; Total ozone; Vertical temperature profile; Atmospherics; Global warming; Ozone; Ozone layer; Sulfur compounds; Superalloys; Troposphere; Atmospheric temperature; air temperature; global warming; ozone depletion; remote sensing; stratosphere; temperature profile; total ozone; troposphere; Athens [Attica]; Attica; Greece",,,,,,"Bojkov, R.D., Komhyr, W.D., Lapworth, A., Vanicek, K., (1993) Handbook for Dobson Ozone Data Re-evaluation, , WMO Global Ozone Research and Monitoring Project, Report No 29, WMO/TDK-No.597 (Geneva: World Meteorological Organization); Chandra, S., Varotsos, C.A., Recent trends of the total column ozone-implications for the Mediterranea